KnowledgeBase.Title: Example Dictionary compareNE 004
KnowledgeBase.RelatedFunctions: compare compareEQ compareLE compareGE compareLT compareGT

Example.Description: These examples use the compareNE function to compare two Dictionaries and return the Boolean value, true or false. The corresponding keys and values of each Dictionary are compared to determine whether one Dictionary is equal to the other.

Syntax.Note: The first Dictionary is lesser than the second Dictionary.
